<TITLE> BSMMU patients ransack Ansar camp after manhandling at hospital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 16 (bdnews24.com)--Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital ansar camp was ransacked Monday following the removal of a patient from the hospital's outpatient line. Witnesses said ansar Sultan Ali pushed out of line an elderly patient who came for treatment at the outpatient department of the hospital. Another man whom witnesses named as Jasim, a relative of another patient, who was standing in the same line was also manhandled by the ansar, they said. Sultan then dragged Jasim off to the ansar camp. Later, others who had been in the outpatient line went and ransacked the ansar camp. Police arrived to bring the situation under control. Jasim told bdnews24.com: "When the ansar member pushed the old patient, he stumbled onto my wife. When I protested the incident I was taken to the ansar camp." Ansar officer Tayeb Ali, who is in charge of the camp, said:, "The unpleasant incident occurred over a trifling matter." bdnew
